1
00:00:09,625 --> 00:00:11,750
[JUNICHIRO]
I have YD.

2
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:13,583
You say you've
never heard of it?

3
00:00:13,666 --> 00:00:17,833
What? I like wearing yukata
on dates? Or yummy dinners?

4
00:00:17,916 --> 00:00:20,500
Wrong! It's a
debilitating illness

5
00:00:20,583 --> 00:00:23,625
where you can only do
what you yearn to do.

6
00:00:26,291 --> 00:00:31,291
[laughter and jeering]

7
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:48,000
[YOU RED POND]
♪ Amazing grace ♪

8
00:00:48,083 --> 00:01:00,666
♪ How sweet the sound
that saved a wretch... ♪

9
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,958
[JUNICHIRO grunts]

10
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:45,958
Man. I am so glad that's over.

11
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:46,875
[SUZUNE]
Hey, bro.

12
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:49,541
Huh? Hey there,
sis. What's up?

13
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:52,708
[JUNICHIRO]
Uh...

14
00:02:52,791 --> 00:02:54,125
Actually, I was
looking for you.

15
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:56,208
I've got someone here
I want you to meet.

16
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:59,000
Oh, yeah, this girl has me
for physics, doesn't she?

17
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:03,166
Yep. Allow me to introduce
my friend Kanan Chinami.

18
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:05,333
She's got some physics
questions, and since I said

19
00:03:05,416 --> 00:03:07,833
you were my brother, she was
hoping you could help her.

20
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:09,208
Are you kidding?

21
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:11,250
I already finished teaching
my classes for the day.

22
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:12,833
[SUZUNE]
Hnn--hyah!

23
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:14,541
Are we about to have a problem?

24
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:16,458
Oh no, everything's
just dandy, thank you.

25
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:18,750
That's right. Do you always
have to go out of your way

26
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,166
to make my life so difficult?

27
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:21,708
Do you always have
to wave a bat at me

28
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:23,500
just because I'm being myself?

29
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:25,875
[SUZUNE] Whatever. Kanan
needs to make a great score

30
00:03:25,958 --> 00:03:27,083
on her next physics exam,

31
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:29,250
and you're her best shot
at achieving that.

32
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:31,000
So you are going to help her.

33
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:33,083
Why do I have to help her?
I just wanna go home

34
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:36,083
and work on my blog. I'm losing
followers left and right.

35
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:38,083
[SUZUNE] It's your
job to help her.

36
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:40,333
Her grade's gotta be in
the top 10 in her class.

37
00:03:40,416 --> 00:03:42,791
If it's not, she has to
miss You Red Pond's concert.

38
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:44,083
[JUNICHIRO]
You who what?

39
00:03:44,166 --> 00:03:45,250
[SUZUNE] You Red Pond
is the name

40
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:47,375
of Kanan's favorite
American singer.

41
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:49,416
She's desperate to
go to the concert.

42
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,250
So you're gonna have
to forget about your blog

43
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:53,041
and help her
get her grade up.

44
00:03:53,125 --> 00:03:54,833
I'm not getting what
her grades have to do

45
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:56,208
with her going to a concert.

46
00:03:56,291 --> 00:03:58,750
Kanan's parents are super
strict about school,

47
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:00,541
so she really needs to
wow them with her grades

48
00:04:00,625 --> 00:04:03,000
to be able to go. So?

49
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:04,708
Hm. Fine.

50
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:07,750
I guess since I'm supposed to
be a teacher and everything.

51
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,666
Eh... Can you tell me
what you need help with?

52
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,291
[JUNICHIRO gasps]
Great Scott!

53
00:04:13,375 --> 00:04:15,833
She just texted me.
"I don't understand the part

54
00:04:15,916 --> 00:04:18,000
about how physics works
or why and stuff."

55
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:19,541
[JUNICHIRO stammers]

56
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:22,291
[JUNICHIRO] Am I the only one
who saw how weird that was?

57
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:24,750
So, uh, yeah, what's the deal
with that whole exchange?

58
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:27,958
[SUZUNE] Do not make me hit you
for asking a stupid question.

59
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:30,791
[JUNICHIRO] She never speaks?

60
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:33,208
[SUZUNE] Nope. Back in
middle school, Kanan and I

61
00:04:33,291 --> 00:04:35,458
were classmates and good
friends, but she's never

62
