her a lot for her voice.

66
00:04:42,791 --> 00:04:45,541
So she stopped talking and only
communicates through texts now.

67
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:46,875
[JUNICHIRO]
Hmm...

68
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:49,208
Also, it doesn't help
that she's really pretty.

69
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:51,708
Along with the "no talking"
thing, she's kinda famous.

70
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,666
[SUZUNE blows]

71
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:56,500
Mm... Now people treat
her like a challenge.

72
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:59,208
Loads of guys have tried dumb
stuff to get her to talk.

73
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:01,791
They've brought her flowers,
taken her on dates.

74
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:03,833
They're so cocky,
but no one's convinced her

75
00:05:03,916 --> 00:05:06,250
they deserve to hear
the sound of her voice yet.

76
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:09,000
Nobody can get
her to talk, huh?

77
00:05:09,083 --> 00:05:11,208
It seems like a lot of
hassle that could easily

78
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:14,208
be taken care of if she
would just talk. Y'know?

79
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:16,625
Oh, please don't be
that way, Junichiro.

80
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:18,708
It's supposed to be
a big secret, but...

81
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:21,333
Her voice actually
sounds like...

82
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:25,500
[JUNICHIRO]
Whaaaaat?

83
00:05:25,583 --> 00:05:28,041
Why didn't you mention the
most important fact until now?!

84
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:31,916
Kanan has absolutely no choice
in the matter! She must speak!

85
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,416
Hmph!

86
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,458
[SUZUNE groans]

87
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:39,125
[indistinct chatter]

88
00:05:39,208 --> 00:05:42,416
[JUNICHIRO] Miss Kanan Chinami.
Miss Kanan Chinami.

89
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,541
Please report to the
science storage room.

90
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:46,916
I repeat, Class 2-3...

91
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:02,833
All right, Kanan.
Let's conduct an experiment.

92
00:06:02,916 --> 00:06:05,416
My sister finally
told me your secret.

93
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:08,041
And that look confirms it.
So I've set up

94
00:06:08,125 --> 00:06:11,250
a first-rate dialogue
recording session for you.

95
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,375
Oh, the microphone?
It's vitally important

96
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:15,250
that I hear your anime voice.

97
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:18,791
I've taken the storage room and
made it into a recording studio.

98
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:22,875
I hope you realize I've
gone to a lot of effort.

99
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:26,166
The acoustics
are perfection. Hm?

100
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:32,666
Huh? You wonder why I
would go to such lengths?

101
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,375
Because it is
absolutely imperative

102
00:06:34,458 --> 00:06:36,791
that I hear your voice!

103
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:39,875
There are over 2,000 voice
actors working in the field.

104
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,833
But amongst those,
probably fewer than 10

105
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:45,708
are actually the "chosen ones."
A natural anime voice

106
00:06:45,791 --> 00:06:48,583
is so rare even otaku
like me seldom hear one.

107
00:06:48,666 --> 00:06:50,583
If only you would whisper
something in my ear!

108
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:53,041
I would give my life to
hear such a pure sound!

109
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:54,541
But then which line
would I like to hear?

110
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:55,958
How would I ever
be able to choose?

111
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,125
How can a father
pick a favorite child?

112
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:01,500
Maybe Sergeant Saunders'
signature line, "Bakyuun"?

113
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:03,916
And maybe after that... Huh?

114
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:07,250
[JUNICHIRO]
Hm?

115
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:14,250
[JUNICHIRO] That is correct.
None at all. Worry-free.

116
00:07:14,333 --> 00:07:15,791
You're beginning to
understand how important

117
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:18,708
your voice is to a
true otaku like me.

118
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:20,875
Behold! The super
priceless recording script

119
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:24,916
for episode one of "Magical
Cannon Girl Bura-Kura"!

120
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,916
So are you ready to begin?

121
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,875
[JUNICHIRO groans]

122
00:07:28,958 --> 00:07:32,375
[JUNICHIRO grunts]

123
00:07:32,458 --> 00:07:34,416
All right, Kanan Chinami.

124
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:38,916
Your voice is the prize,
and I'm playing to win.

125
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,916
Yes! Everything is going
exactly as I'd planned.

126
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,125
It's time to start the lesson!

127
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,958
Mornin', jerk. So what did
you say to Kanan yesterday?

128
00:07:51,041 --> 00:07:53,750
A bunch of stuff. Did she
tell you something was wrong?

129
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,125
I've been texting her all day

130
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:58,125
and she's only replied
with silence. Total silence.

131
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:00,333
"Silence"?

132
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:02,958
That is an unexpected
complication.

133
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:05,583
You already knew that she was
super sensitive about her voice.

134
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:08,833
You should be teaching her
and not harassing her about it!

135
00:08:08,916 --> 00:08:10,958
[JUNICHIRO] That can't be
what you really think, is it?

136
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:12,541
[SUZUNE]
Uhh...

137
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:15,208
[JUNICHIRO] Are you sure it's
best to let her go on like this?

138
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:18,666
Well, maybe not, But how could
we convince her otherwise?

139
00:08:18,750 --> 00:08:21,875
Okay, that settles it. You get
to help me teach this lesson.

140
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,458
[SUZUNE]
Hm?

141
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:26,041
[JUNICHIRO] We are talking about
a priceless anime voice here.

142
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:29,250
As if I'm going to let a
miracle like that pass me by!

143
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:30,583
Why do I feel like
you're roping me

144
00:08:30,666 --> 00:08:32,791
into a scheme I'll
regret in the end?

145
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:34,541
[TV REPORTER]
Next up in the news hour...

146
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:37,708
You Red Pond, the world famous
singer, has begun her world tour

147
00:08:37,791 --> 00:08:41,583
tonight in Miami, Florida, USA,
and venues are selling out.

148
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:44,041
She will be
visiting 130 countries

149
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:46,291
with her amazing voice. Rum--

150
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:17,208
[JUNICHIRO] So the physics
struggle is real, huh?

151
00:09:17,291 --> 00:09:19,375
There's only one week
left before the test.

152
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:21,750
How much do you think you
can learn all on your own?

153
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,333
And I hate to be a
downer, but it looks

154
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,666
like you're not
making much progress.

155
00:09:27,583 --> 00:09:31,000
[JUNICHIRO] No response at all?
Awfully cold of you.

156
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:42,666
[DOOR VOICE] You must say
the password, gero gero.

157
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:44,708
Oh, looks like I forgot
to mention something.

158
00:09:44,791 --> 00:09:47,625
The doors in the library
have been modified by me.

159
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:49,166
The locks are voice-activated,

160
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,958
but don't worry.
All you have to do is say

161
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:53,958
Sergeant Saunders' famous
catchphrase and they'll ope--

162
00:10:00,958 --> 00:10:04,500
Hm. So there's still some
work to do on this project.

163
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:10,375
Oh, Mrs. Chinami, you don't seem
old enough to have a teenager!

164
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:11,416
That's kind of
you to say, sir!

165
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:12,541
It's easy when it's the truth!

166
00:10:12,625 --> 00:10:13,875
Be careful not to
flatter me too much!

167
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:15,000
I didn't think Kanan would
have such a great mom!

168
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:16,500
Hey, girl! Are you
surprised to see us?

169
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,208
We were all waiting for you!

170
00:10:18,291 --> 00:10:20,416
[KANAN'S MOTHER] Kanan,
come sit with your teacher!

171
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:24,000
If I'd been expecting Kanan's
teacher this afternoon,

172
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:26,458
I would've prepared a
special dinner for all of you!

173
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:28,166
Please, it's my fault,
I assure you.

174
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,000
There's no reason
to scold Miss Kanan.

175
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:32,041
I found myself suddenly
overcome with the need

176
00:10:32,125 --> 00:10:34,750
to help this eager student, and
the whole plan was last minute,

177
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,666
so I didn't give her a
chance to prepare you!

178
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:38,875
Kanan's struggled with
physics for so long.

179
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:41,000
She's lucky to have
such a dedicated teacher.

180
00:10:41,083 --> 00:10:42,791
With your assistance,
I know she'll rise

181
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,125
to the top of her class!

182
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,916
Don't worry--
you can count on me!

183
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,125
I am, after all, the number
one physics teacher.

184
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:50,583
[KANAN'S MOTHER] How perfectly
charming and dramatic!

185
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:52,375
[SUZUNE and KANAN'S
MOTHER laugh]

186
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,166
We're not gonna abandon you.

187
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:57,541
I anticipated a reaction
like this from you.

188
00:10:57,625 --> 00:10:58,791
Suzune, you're on.

189
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:00,333
[SUZUNE]
Hm!

190
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,875
Since she's used to speaking
with you, Suzune will translate

191
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:06,250
so you can let us know
how you really feel.

192
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:09,000
Now, please, go ahead
and let it all out.

193
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,541
"Can you please leave
and get out of my life?

194
00:11:13,625 --> 00:11:16,041
In case you hadn't noticed,
I actually have to study.

195
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,791
I don't want anything to do
with you or your schemes."

196
00:11:18,875 --> 00:11:20,958
[JUNICHIRO] Are you sure
that's what you want?

197
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:22,500
[SUZUNE hums]

198
00:11:22,583 --> 00:11:25,041
"Neither my fingers nor your
sister's voice stuttered.

199
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:27,708
Besides, why did the two of you
come all the way out here?"

200
00:11:27,791 --> 00:11:30,125
Obviously, as a concerned
teacher, it's my duty

201
00:11:30,208 --> 00:11:33,583
to do everything in my power
to improve your test scores.

202
00:11:33,666 --> 00:11:34,833
"Say what?"

203
00:11:34,916 --> 00:11:37,458
What we have here is
a cool anime premise.

204
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,208
I'm the hero and your
voice is a McGuffin

205
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:40,500
and just like Sergeant Saunders,

206
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:43,166
I'll fight through
every last challenge.

207
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:45,166
And just before the
closing credit song begins,

208
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:46,708
you'll speak to me!

209
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,166
"I would never
make that deal!

210
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:51,833
It doesn't matter
how special you think

211
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:54,666
my voice might sound because
I will never speak again!"

212
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:56,500
[JUNICHIRO]
Like I said...

213
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:59,625
Are you sure that's really how
you want this all to play out?

214
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:01,500
You're the one who
said you "have to" go

215
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:03,708
to You Red Pond's
concert, right?

216
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,458
And correct me if I'm wrong,
but didn't you say

217
00:12:05,541 --> 00:12:07,958
you need to get your grades
up in order to do that?

218
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:10,041
And we all know you can't
possibly accomplish that

219
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:12,125
without my generous assistance.

220
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:14,208
All I'm asking for is
that you kindly allow me

221
00:12:14,291 --> 00:12:16,416
to hear your precious
voice. No biggie.

222
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:18,333
So, let's make a deal!

223
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:22,208
"You talk a pretty big game.

224
00:12:22,291 --> 00:12:25,333
I don't see how it's possible
to make the top ten so fast."

225
00:12:25,416 --> 00:12:27,583
[JUNICHIRO] Trust me, my YD
is an asset. It means that

226
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:32,166
when I actually yearn to do
something, I totally deliver.

227
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:34,750
How about this? If I can't
tutor you into the top ten,

228
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:37,833
I will make a solemn
vow to quit. Sound fair?

229
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:41,333
[SUZUNE gasps]
That's not necessary!

230
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:43,125
So, whaddaya say?

231
00:12:46,583 --> 00:12:50,541
Heh... Huzzah!
Then we have a deal!

232
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:53,791
I took the liberty of
analyzing all of your grades

