00:12:55,791 --> 00:12:57,250
It seems that where
your previous teachers

235
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:58,583
failed you is in
your understanding

236
00:12:58,666 --> 00:13:01,250
of quadratic functions
and multipliers.

237
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:03,250
Naturally, weakness in
those areas would put you

238
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:05,958
at a disadvantage when studying
wave equations and dynamics,

239
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:08,416
which ultimately is why your
grades have been going nowhere.

240
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,083
So I built this
especially for you

241
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:12,833
to work with your shortcomings.

242
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,416
[SUZUNE]
Huh?

243
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,250
[JUNICHIRO] Kanan Quest,
the ultra-personalized

244
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:19,791
educational video game
built for your success!

245
00:13:19,875 --> 00:13:21,458
This program calculates
your weaknesses

246
00:13:21,541 --> 00:13:23,208
and creates problems instantly!

247
00:13:23,291 --> 00:13:27,416
As your understanding deepens,
the questions intensify.

248
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,375
If you can get past
level 8 in this game,

249
00:13:29,458 --> 00:13:32,583
you should be able to at
least get an 80 on your test.

250
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,500
[JUNICHIRO]
You're stressing too much.

251
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:23,416
Just like any RPG, if you keep
grinding, you'll get stronger.

252
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:26,375
Those monsters you're facing now
will be trash mobs in no time.

253
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:29,541
It'll be easy! Huh?

254
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:33,250
She says it's not easy
for her, but... hmm.

255
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,916
Hm?

256
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Okay. Think I got it.

257
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:52,083
[knock at the door]

258
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:54,625
[JUNICHIRO]
I'm coming in.

259
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,625
Here, since you said it was
too hard, I put together

260
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:59,333
a brand new custom
system overnight.

261
00:15:06,625 --> 00:15:09,500
[JUNICHIRO] Check out that FMV!
You'd think Square-Enix made it!

262
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:13,625
Anyway, I call it
Kanan Fantasy 2!

263
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:15,416
I added a debug function
to help the game

264
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,708
further develop your skills.

265
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,166
It analyzes your
weaknesses in order

266
00:15:19,250 --> 00:15:22,333
to help you overcome them
with clearer questions.

267
00:15:22,416 --> 00:15:24,291
There's no way your
grades won't improve now!

268
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:26,500
Also, can you believe
those graphics?

269
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:29,416
Your game is now in high-def 3D,
which adds a level of realism,

270
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:32,166
depth, and complexity to the
physics problems you encounter.

271
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:34,041
All of which should
encourage thinking--

272
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:36,625
[JUNICHIRO grunts]

273
00:15:44,583 --> 00:15:47,458
[JUNICHIRO groans softly]

274
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:50,916
Did I fall asleep or something?
Sorry, I guess I must've been

275
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,750
pretty exhausted after
the last few nights.

276
00:15:57,125 --> 00:16:00,583
Why are you sorry? In the end,
it's my fault that I haven't

277
00:16:00,666 --> 00:16:03,333
been able to teach you
physics effectively enough--

278
00:16:08,291 --> 00:16:09,708
[JUNICHIRO gasps]

279
00:16:09,791 --> 00:16:11,291
[JUNICHIRO] You have to
get into the top ten...

280
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:14,375
Otherwise, it wouldn't
be right to accept that.

281
00:16:14,458 --> 00:16:16,250
As an otaku, I take
pride in making

282
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:19,458
large payments for
things of true value.

283
00:16:19,541 --> 00:16:21,833
I appreciate the
gesture, though.

284
00:16:28,583 --> 00:16:30,458
[JUNICHIRO] You know,
I only got 5 out of 100

285
00:16:30,541 --> 00:16:33,250
on my first physics test.

286
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:36,666
I thought the whole subject was
boring and irrelevant at first,

287
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:39,416
but I had this cool idea
to build an "Anywhere Door."

288
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:41,416
People told me I could never
make something like that

289
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,041
without physics,
so I studied physics

290
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:45,250
because it was
something I had to do.

291
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,125
I always do what
I "yearn to do,"

292
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,416
but that's not necessarily
what I'm naturally good at,

293
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,958
or even what I can
already accomplish.

294
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:53,416
In order to realize
a bigger goal,

295
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:56,416
sometimes I have to do
something I'm bad at.

296
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,708
So in a way,
we're the same.

297
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:12,750
[BOY A] Whoa, that's
a total anime voice!

298
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,750
[BOY B] Is that
really her real voice?

299
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:15,750
Are you sure it's not edited?

300
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:17,125
[BOY C] This is
godlike! Sort of!

301
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:20,125
[BOY A] Her voice is
in the 2.5th dimension!

302
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:25,250
[GIRL A] Wow, Kanan,
you're like super popular!

303
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:26,583
Look at all the comments!

304
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:28,041
[GIRL B] I always thought
your voice was funny,

305
00:17:28,125 --> 00:17:31,041
but I didn't know what to
call it! "Anime voice," huh?

306
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:38,916
[GIRLS laugh]

307
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:42,000
[GIRL B] Huh? The comments
just stopped. What happened?

308
00:17:42,083 --> 00:17:43,208
[GIRL A] They were
coming into the video

309
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:46,041
like a total flood
until a second ago.

310
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:48,208
[GIRL C]
Hey, look!

311
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:49,291
[OTHER GIRLS]
Huh?

312
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:51,833
[YOU RED POND]
♪ Amazing grace... ♪

313
00:17:51,916 --> 00:17:54,125
[GIRL C] It's You Red Pond's
concert, streaming live!

314
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:56,750
I guess everyone went
to watch that instead.

315
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,291
[GIRLS ooh and ahh]

316
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:06,166
[YOU RED POND]
♪ ...that saved a wre-- ♪

317
00:18:15,958 --> 00:18:18,958
[SUZUNE] So. Kanan's
big exam is happening today.

318
00:18:19,041 --> 00:18:20,125
Do you think she'll
do good enough

319
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:22,083
to be able to go to the concert?

320
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:23,333
[JUNICHIRO laughs]

321
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:24,541
You're looking smug!

322
00:18:24,625 --> 00:18:26,583
Hail to the King!

323
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:31,166
Ah, let me see...
She got up to... Level 10?!

324
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:33,291
Wow, that's really fantastic!

325
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:36,541
Yeah, all she had to do was get
past level 8, but she rocked it!

326
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:39,291
Awesome! So she's actually
prepared to do well on the test?

327
00:18:39,375 --> 00:18:41,041
Why, yes, indeed, she is!

328
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:42,291
[phone chimes]

329
00:18:42,375 --> 00:18:45,333
Is that my phone?
A little early for a text.

330
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:49,208
I guess I better get
a move on, and quick!

331
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:53,833
[JUNICHIRO] Good morning.
Is everything okay?

332
00:18:53,916 --> 00:18:55,541
[phone chimes]

333
00:18:55,625 --> 00:18:57,375
[JUNICHIRO]
Uh, let me just read.

334
00:18:57,458 --> 00:19:00,916
"Mr. Kagami, I hate my voice
more than I can tell you."

335
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,583
Kanan, that's the only thing
I'm sure about with you.

336
00:19:03,666 --> 00:19:06,041
That's why you have such a
fascination with You Red Pond,

337
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:08,791
isn't it? And why you're
set on going to her concert?

338
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:13,083
"She saved me.
So ever since that day,

339
00:19:13,166 --> 00:19:15,541
anytime I have the
opportunity to hear her sing,

340
00:19:15,625 --> 00:19:18,250
I'm able to instantly
forget all my problems."

341
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:19,750
That's fine and dandy,
I suppose,

342
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:23,041
but that's not really the
issue we're tackling here.

343
00:19:23,125 --> 00:19:24,375
[phone chimes]

344
00:19:24,458 --> 00:19:26,375
"Her voice is so heavenly,
clear, and beautiful,

345
00:19:26,458 --> 00:19:29,833
it's just like the total and
complete opposite of mine."

346
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:31,291
Well, if you want my opinion,

347
00:19:31,375 --> 00:19:34,916
heavenly, beautiful voices
are totally overrated.

348
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,458
Heh!

349
00:19:37,541 --> 00:19:44,916
♪ Amazing grace,
how sweet the sound ♪

350
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:50,000
♪ that saved a
wretch like me! ♪

351
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:51,833
Yeah.

352
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:56,083
Ya see? I'm glad my voice is
nothing like You Red Pond's.

353
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:00,333
So you still don't get it.

354
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:12,166
[ASSORTMENT OF VOICES, ONE AFTER
ANOTHER] And you know what?

355
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:17,500
[ASSORTMENT OF VOICES, ONE AFTER
ANOTHER] And you know what?

356
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:20,708
[JUNICHIRO] Would you be happy
with any of these voices?

357
00:20:20,791 --> 00:20:24,166
I have a famously bad voice,
but you know what I love?

358
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:26,750
Karaoke. I go with friends,

359
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:30,916
and they still have fun
despite the fact that I suck.

360
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,458
You get it now? People like
and enjoy different things.

361
00:20:34,541 --> 00:20:36,833
And that's totally okay.

362
00:20:36,916 --> 00:20:39,750
Miyazaki thinks otaku are
the worst. That doesn't mean

363
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:42,958
his films are bad or that
something's wrong with me.

364
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:46,458
All that logical stuff aside,
my point is simple.

365
00:20:46,541 --> 00:20:49,416
We had an agreement.
Will you honor it?

366
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:54,750
I want to hear your voice,
no matter how it sounds.

367
00:20:56,958 --> 00:20:59,916
[KANAN whimpers]

368
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:07,250
[KANAN whimpers]

369
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:10,041
That's it for today's lesson.

370
00:21:10,125 --> 00:21:12,291
I have really high hopes
for you. I think you're

371
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:15,000
definitely going to get
that high score you need--

372
00:21:19,083 --> 00:21:21,208
Bakyuun!

373
00:21:21,291 --> 00:21:24,458
[JUNICHIRO gasps]

374
00:21:29,416 --> 00:21:32,916
Good god!
She utterly stunned me!

375
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,958
Now go get 'em,
Anime Girl!

376
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:41,916
[KANAN giggles]

377
00:21:48,083 --> 00:21:55,083
Uh? What the hell have I done?!
I forgot to record her voice!

378
00:21:55,166 --> 00:21:57,041
[KANAN giggles]

379
00:23:30,666 --> 00:23:33,791
[KANAN] Bakyuun!
This is Kanan Chinami!

380
00:23:33,875 --> 00:23:36,125
I'm talking again,
thanks to Mr. Kagami!

381
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:38,958
This anime voice is part
of who I am, after all!

382
00:23:39,041 --> 00:23:41,291
In the next episode,
Mr. Kagami meets

383
00:23:41,375 --> 00:23:43,416
a gothic-lolita girl in Akiba.

384
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:47,166
She is Sachiko Tanaka,
a twisted truant in our class.

385
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:50,333
Period 8, "The Truant
is a Grand Master."

386
00:23:50,416 --> 00:23:52,250
Her alternate
identity is revealed,

387
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:54,875
along with her rivalry
with Makina Momozono!

388
00:23:54,958 --> 00:23:57,583
Mr. Kagami's got his
hands full with this one!

